result.name: Exercise Science, BS - Clinical Exercise & Rehabilitation Specialist

templateAssets.content:
Thank you for your interest in Sacramento State!


This articulation agreement displays the lower-division courses required in the major: Sacramento State courses on the left and approved (articulated) transfer courses on the right. Although completion of the coursework listed below is not mandatory prior to admission, students are advised to complete as much lower-division course preparation as possible prior to transfer.


Additional Resources:

  • See the University Catalog for the full listing of degree requirements for this major.
  • Visit our Sac State Apply page for more information about our campus!
  • Visit the Admissions website for current transfer admission requirements.
  • Connect with an Admissions Counselor.

1. Students must earn a "C-" grade or higher in all courses required in the major.
  2. Students who are selected for admission to the university are admitted as "Pre-Exercise Science" students. To declare the major, students must complete BIO 10, BIO 22, CHEM 1A or CHEM 6A, and CHEM 1B or CHEM 6B with a grade of "C-" or higher and have an overall GPA of 2.0. Only first and second attempts will be considered.
  3. In addition to the pre-major courses, a minimum of 13 units are required for the Clinical Exercise and Rehabilitation Specialist concentration. The recommended lower-division courses students may select from are listed below. Additional upper-division course options are also available after transfer. It is recommended students select courses for their concentration in consultation with an advisor.
  4. Foreign Language Graduation Requirement Exemption: Students graduating with a Bachelor of Science in Exercise Science will not be subject to the University's Foreign Language Graduation Requirement. Students who change major may be subject to the University's Foreign Language Graduation Requirement.
  5. For additional information, please visit: Department of Kinesiology.
